Definition: in a hurried or hasty manner
Example: the way they buried him so hurriedly was disgraceful; hastily, he scanned the headlines; sold in haste and at a sacrifice
Synonyms: unhurriedly, adj, all, hurried, hastily, hasty, in_haste, in, a, or, manner, the, way, they, buried, him, so, was, disgraceful, he, scanned, headlines, sold, haste, and, at, sacrifice
Category: adv.all
